When his son dies returning from Tibet's salt lakes, Tinle blames Karma, his son's friend, refuses to give Karma his blessing as the new chief, and organizes a rival caravan to take the salt to lower Nepal to trade for grain. He, a few old men, his son's widow, his grandson, and his second son, a monk, set out on the arduous journey. Fearing storms, Karma has led his caravan out of the village before the auspicious day ordained by the lamas. Tinle's group catches Karma's before the final pass; the two stubborn men lock wills with Tinle's grandson watching.
Various tales in the lives of Tokyo slum dwellers, including a mentally deficient young man obsessed with driving his own commuter trolley.

caption.plainText: Akshay Kumar, Naseeruddin Shah, Suniel Shetty, and Raveena Tandon in Mohra (1994)

plotText.plainText: A journalist comes to the aid of a murderer with a life sentence when she makes an appeal in court and although he is given his freedom, they soon discover that there is a grim reason behind his release.

caption.plainText: Billy Bob Thornton, Thomas Jane, James Marsden, Piper Perabo, and Bart the Bear in Into the Grizzly Maze (2015)

plotText.plainText: Two estranged brothers reunite at their childhood home in the Alaskan wild. They set out on a two-day hike and are stalked by an unrelenting grizzly bear.

During the 1700s, pirate Captain Vallo seizes a British warship and gets involved in various money-making schemes involving Caribbean rebels led by El Libre, British envoy Baron Jose Gruda, and a beautiful courtesan named Consuelo.

caption.plainText: Aaron Paul and Josh Wiggins in Haylaz (2014)

plotText.plainText: When Jacob's delinquency leads to his brother Wes being placed with relatives, Jacob and his father Hollis must confront their issues to reunite the family.

originalTitleText.text: Justin and the Knights of Valour

Yetis Bey, an ordinary peasant, tells the story of his struggle against the Byzantine Emperor Illetyus in a humorous way.

plotText.plainText: In the late 1800s, a fanatical religious leader, a renegade Sheriff, and a former prostitute collide in a blood triangle on the rugged plains of the New Mexico Territory.

This film tells the story of a few uneventful days in the life of six pals. Lali, a great fan of America, owns a sandwich stand on the side of the road, called The Glass Tiger. Gaben pinches cars; Fox is a petty swindler; Sanyi a half-wit homeless; Coco can't shut up about getting some dough and going to America; Slimmy keeps playing the saxophone, despite the others' frayed nerves. Gaben talks Lali into buying an old Chevrolet Impala, the real American dream. After the long escapade of getting the car, Lali doesn't even get the chance to try the Chevvy out, because a truck completely demolishes it. Fox in the meantime is looking excitedly for the "Wreck", what he has been trying to sell for big money. But Lali has sold what he thought to be scrap, not good for anything. Fox is threatened by some tough guys to bring it back or pay up. He has to get money at all costs. Coco can think of only one solution. They have to rob the nearby bank. They all get into a car, but the big heist does not work out perfectly.

caption.plainText: Akshay Kumar, Paresh Rawal, Suniel Shetty, and Katrina Kaif in De Dana Dan (2009)

plotText.plainText: Two down on their luck men tries to kidnap a wealthy businesswoman's dog to demand a hefty ransom from her. Things goes haywire when the dog goes missing.
A nightclub singer seeks refuge with gay nuns on dope in a Madrid convent.
A man's life begins to unravel when his mistress brings him a bag of cash.

caption.plainText: Louis de Funès and Jean Marais in Fantômas se déchaîne (1965)

plotText.plainText: When Professor Marchand, a famous scientist, mysteriously disappears, the commissioner, Juve, immediately suspects Fantomas.

A conman Roy, gets dumped by his girl-friend. Then he finds out he has a fatal disease. On the verge of death, he resolves to do some good, by helping his apprentice Dittu hoodwink the mobster who hurt his (Dittu's) family.
A marriage of convenience between a petty gangster and an illegal immigrant he has never met has unforeseen consequences for them both.

caption.plainText: Hilary Swank in The Affair of the Necklace (2001)

plotText.plainText: In pre-Revolutionary France, a young aristocratic woman left penniless by the political unrest in the country must avenge her family's fall from grace by scheming to steal a priceless necklace.

caption.plainText: Groucho Marx, Eve Arden, Chico Marx, and Harpo Marx in Üç Ahbap Çavuşlar Sirkte (1939)

plotText.plainText: The Marx Brothers try to help the owner of a circus recover some stolen funds before he finds himself out of a job.
The Kildren, a group of eternally young fighter pilots, experience the sudden loss of innocence as they battle the enemy in astonishing dogfights above the clouds.

Follow the infamous ninja bandit named Ishikawa Goemon in an epic story. One night while looting treasure from Nanban, Goemon finds a mysterious box hidden inside a secret grave. A forgotten relic from the past containing untold powers.
Ex-Green Beret hapkido expert saves wild horses from being slaughtered for dog food and helps protect a desert "freedom school" for runaway.
Five friends are stalked by a group of mysterious and disturbed individuals while on a road trip looking for the ultimate haunted house attraction.

caption.plainText: Jennifer Jones in The Song of Bernadette (1943)

plotText.plainText: 14-year-old Bernadette Soubirous, living in a small town in the south of 1850s France, claims to have seen a divine vision, prompting extreme skepticism, concern from her family, and religious and political turmoil.

A girl with few real prospects joins a gang, reinventing herself and gaining a sense of self confidence in the process. However, she soon finds that this new life does not necessarily make her any happier.
A businessman with a disfigured face obtains a lifelike mask from his doctor, but the mask starts altering his personality.
A businessman finds himself trapped at a hotel and threatened by women en masse.

The Seven Dwarves live deep within a female-free-zone of the Enchanted Forest, but they cannot resist the innocent charms of Snow White when she enters their world. So when the evil queen (Nina Hagen) abducts her, it is up to the dwarves to save her life.

caption.plainText: Humphrey Bogart, Joel McCrea, Sylvia Sidney, and Claire Trevor in Çıkmaz Sokak (1937)

plotText.plainText: The lives of a young man, a young woman, an notorious gangster, and a group of street kids converge one day in a volatile New York City slum.
Romance blooms between two tricenarians in arrested development: an avid toy collector who is the dark horse of his family and a depressed woman on the rebound.

caption.plainText: Noomi Rapace and Vetle Qvenild Werring in Ölümün Sesi (2011)

plotText.plainText: After a baby monitor picks up another channel, Anna begins reliving the nightmare she'd recently escaped.

caption.plainText: Chris Eigeman, Tushka Bergen, and Taylor Nichols in Barcelona (1994)

plotText.plainText: An American working in Barcelona, having sworn off beautiful women, is forced to be host to his playboy cousin in this witty comedy of good intentions and mixed signals.
Racism collides with corporate greed when nine strangers - one of whom has a bomb - become trapped in a Wall Street elevator.

caption.plainText: Sunny Deol, Ameesha Patel, and Amrish Puri in Gadar: Ek Prem Katha (2001)

plotText.plainText: During the Partition of India in 1947, a Sikh truck driver falls in love with a Muslim girl belonging to an aristocratic family.
A story about Quebec's most famous hockey player, Maurice "The Rocket" Richard, focusing on the struggles of a French Canadian in the National Hockey League dominated by Anglophones.
In a Mennonite community in Mexico, a father's faith is tested when he falls in love with a new woman.

Costantino and Daniele are two friends which have very success with girls. Their wish is to work in the show business and they can achieve their goal when meet Valeria, top model and actress, who offers both guys the chance they are looking for: meet Mr. Giampalmi, an important producer. But the producer is Valeria's father who wants the guys to be cheated...
An ex cop and his ex partner decide to follow up on investigation of a series of murders that ended their careers and shamed them, when identical murders begin again.
An uptight but secretly heartbroken primary school teacher's little white lie about Hollywood coming to see his class' nativity play grows like wildfire in his rag-tag school low on self-esteem.

caption.plainText: Jonathan Pryce and Emma Thompson in Carrington (1995)

plotText.plainText: The platonic relationship between artist Dora Carrington and writer Lytton Strachey in the early twentieth century.
Two old pals reunite for a camping trip in Oregon's Cascade Mountains.

originalTitleText.text: La casa del fin de los tiempos

plotText.plainText: After being wrongly imprisoned for the mysterious, supernatural death of her husband and son, Dulce returns back to her old home to unravel the mystery that has haunted her for so long.
Four friends who are mistreated in a casino try to get revenge by kidnapping the casino's singer.

The story of a berserk, hooded killer who terrorized the border town of Texarkana, Arkansas in 1946--leaving no fewer than five murder victims in his wake. He was never caught. Based on one of America's most baffling murder cases.
A woman seeks revenge on her former lover, who owns a skydiving business.
A photographer is introduced to the world of dominance and submission.
A woman finds herself inexplicably cut off from all human contact when an invisible, unyielding wall suddenly surrounds the landscape.

caption.plainText: Terence Hill and Bud Spencer in Miami Supercops (1985)

plotText.plainText: An ex-con returns to Miami after completing a seven-year sentence for thieving $20,000,000 and is murdered. Two FBI agents are then shipped to Miami to investigate the case under the guise of cops.

Sex and love. Some seek it, some need it, some spurn it, and some pay for it, but we're all involved in it. Set on one afternoon on Hampstead Heath, London, this movie investigates the minutiae of seven couples. What makes us tick?
In 1793, as the Terror begins in France, Georges Danton, a champion-of-the-people, returns to clash against Maximilien Robespierre and his extremist party.

caption.plainText: Nelson Eddy and Susanna Foster in Phantom of the Opera (1943)

plotText.plainText: An acid-scarred composer rises from the Paris sewers to boost his favorite opera understudy's career.

caption.plainText: Rosel Zech in Veronika Voss'un Tutkusu (1982)

plotText.plainText: Partially based on the life of Sybille Schmitz, who found fame under the Nazi regime, but whose career was destroyed afterward. Veronika Voss is a once prominent UFA actress, kept by her doctor, who raises suspicion in a sports journalist.
Felix is a legendary prankster who gets expelled from his high school and, with the help of his friends, will stop at nothing to hide it from his parents.

caption.plainText: Angus Scrimm in Phantasm IV: Oblivion (1998)

plotText.plainText: Mike travels through time and dimensions to find the Tall Man's origins.

Set in the Watts area of Los Angeles, a slaughterhouse worker must suspend his emotions to continue working at a job he finds repugnant, and then he finds he has little sensitivity for the family he works so hard to support.

Umay is a young woman of Turkish descent, fighting for an independent and self-determined life in Germany against her family's resistance. Her struggle initiates a dynamic that results in a life-threatening situation.

caption.plainText: Antonio Banderas, Melanie Griffith, and Daryl Hannah in Çifte Oyun (1995)

Two shoeshine boys in postwar Rome, Italy save up to buy a horse, but their involvement as dupes in a burglary lands them in juvenile prison; the experience take a devastating toll on their friendship.

Cemal is a man who lives with his father in Akhisar town of Manisa and works in his own barber shop. Cemal, who seems to be at his own pace, is in trouble, and even he doesn't know what's going on. On the other hand, in this town where almost everyone knows each other, seemingly ordinary people have extraordinary powers.

caption.plainText: Matt Dillon in City of Ghosts (2002)

plotText.plainText: A New York insurance man searches for his crooked business partner in Cambodia.

titleText.text: Komt een vrouw bij de dokter

originalTitleText.text: Komt een vrouw bij de dokter

caption.plainText: Barry Atsma and Carice van Houten in Komt een vrouw bij de dokter (2009)

plotText.plainText: A serial adulterer faces his demons when his loving wife falls severely ill.

plotText.plainText: A wealthy plantation owner is captivated by a mysterious woman with a shady past.
A mockumentary following an ambitious TV network executive trying to produce a controversial reality show where contestants play Russian Roulette.

A space traveler from the Earth of the 22th century - without wars, poverty and oppression - crashes on an unknown planet. Politically and economically that planet similar to the totalitarian human states of the 20th century.
When an L.A. born American citizen is mistaken for a Mexican illegal alien and deported to Mexico, he has to do everything he can to get across the border.

caption.plainText: Romy Schneider and Karlheinz Böhm in aşkın kanunu var (1956)

Residents of an enclosed neighborhood in the middle of Mexico DF are shocked by a violent crime, and for one resident in particular, young Alejandro, the drama is ratcheted up when he encounters the lone kid who escaped the event and is hiding out within the neighborhood's borders.
A doctor kidnaps a young couple and forces them into a game of torment that slowly extinguishes their hopes for survival.

Suburban America gone haywire. In the midst of a serial abductor/killer's rampage, a beautiful young teen, Riley Lawson, goes missing. When her desperate parents, Will and Kate, are contacted by her kidnapper, an insufferable FBI Special Agent takes charge of the case.But, from deep within the psychopathic subterranean world created by Otis, Riley turns the tables on her tormentor, manages to escape and to contact her parents. And, fed up with the tragi-comic inability of the FBI to find their girl, Will, Kate, and Riley's brother, Reed decide to take matters - and justice - into their own hands.

caption.plainText: Charlotte Gainsbourg and Charlotte Rampling in Kuzey Faresi (2005)

plotText.plainText: After developing a flying web-cam Alain has his boss and wife over for dinner. She turns up to be very rude, and the same night Alain finds a live rare Scandinavian lemming clogging up the kitchen sink. The night things start going wrong.

caption.plainText: Terence Hill and Bud Spencer in Devlerin öfkesi (1972)

plotText.plainText: A bush-flying duo crash-land in the heart of the Peruvian jungle where an unscrupulous speculator controls a precious emerald source and an entire mining community. Can they right the wrongs, and in the process, manage to make a profit?
A screenwriter travels to an abandoned house to finish a script on time, but a series of strange events lead her to a psychological breakdown.

caption.plainText: Tyra Banks, Bill Bellamy, French Stewart, and Bridgette Wilson-Sampras in Love Stinks (1999)

plotText.plainText: Seth Winnick has it all: a successful career in television, good friends, and a passionate relationship with beautiful Chelsea. However, when he fails to make a timely marriage proposal, Chelsea tries to make his life hell.

plotText.plainText: The biological and adoptive mothers of a young boy are involved in a bitter, controversial custody battle.
INFECTION takes place in a dark, isolated hospital, where a doctor's mistake has led to dire consequences for a patient.

caption.plainText: Bette Davis and Leslie Howard in İnsanın Esareti (1934)

plotText.plainText: A young man finds himself attracted to a cold, unfeeling waitress who might ultimately destroy them both.

In the city of Suddenly, three gangsters trap the Benson family in their own house, on the top of a hill nearby the railroad station, with the intention of killing the president of the USA.

A corrupt border Agent decides to clean up his act when an impoverished woman's baby is put up for sale on the black market.

plotText.plainText: An ambitious scientist invents an eye drop formula that grants him X-ray vision, but his new powers have disastrous consequences.

caption.plainText: Rita Johnson, Evelyn Keyes, and Robert Montgomery in Here Comes Mr. Jordan (1941)

plotText.plainText: Boxer Joe Pendleton dies 50 years too soon due to a heavenly mistake, and is given a new life as a millionaire playboy.

caption.plainText: Asia Argento in Il fantasma dell'opera (1998)

plotText.plainText: Gory remake of the Gaston Leroux classic story, only this time, the phantom is not disfigured, but a man who was raised by rats deep under the Paris Opera House.
A thriller about a Copenhagen cop who moves to a small town after having a nervous breakdown.
The daily routine of cocaine dealer Priest who wants to score one more super deal and retire.

caption.plainText: Oliver Platt and Stanley Tucci in The Impostors (1998)

plotText.plainText: Wrongly accused of physically abusing a fellow actor, starving thespians Arthur and Maurice find themselves pursued by the law aboard a cruise ship.

A British Army officer resigns, burning his last-day summons to war in the Sudan. Accusing him of cowardice, his girlfriend and three friends give him white feathers. To gain redemption, he shadows his friends to save their lives.

caption.plainText: Lucy Deakins in The Boy Who Could Fly (1986)

plotText.plainText: An autistic boy who dreams of flying touches everyone he meets, including a new family who has moved in after their father dies.
